Package jsat.graphing

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CategoryPlot
    Plots a given data set and color codes the data points by their class category.
    ClassificationPlot
    A plotting tool to visualize the classification results on a 2 dimensional data set.
    Graph2D
    Graph2D is a component for drawing using x and y numeric values, that will be automatically converted into the correct coordinates of the image.
    Histogram  
    ParallelCoordinatesPlot
    A plot for visualizing multi dimensional data sets.
    ProgressPanel
    Basic Progress Panel
    QQPlotData
    Performs a QQ plot to compare the distribution of two sets of univariate data that have the same number of data points.
    QQPlotDistribution
    Creates a new QQ plot to compare a data set against a specified distribution
    ReachabilityPlot
    A reachability plot is a type of visualization that shows the reachability of each data point in a specially sorted order.
    ROCPlot
    ROCPlot provides a simple means by which an Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC) curve can be ploted for one or more classifiers.
    ScatterPlot
    A scatter plot to visualize 2 dimensional data sets.
    ScatterplotMatrix
    A matrix of scatter plots showing the relations between each combination of attributes in the data set
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Graph2D.PointShape
    The different supported point shapes that can be drawn
